[0.978, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[0.013, "o", "/usr/bin/mysql_secure_installation: Deprecated program name. It will be removed in a future release, use 'mariadb-secure-installation' instead\r\n"]
[0.031, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "NOTE: MariaDB is secure by default. Running this script is mostly\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "      unecessary and it will likely be removed in a future release,\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "      but it is for now preserved for backwards compatibility.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Enter root user password or leave blank:\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.013, "o", "Enter current password for root (enter for none): "]
[5.207, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.148, "o", "OK, successfully used password, moving on...\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Setting the root password or using the unix_socket ensures that nobody\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "can log into the MariaDB root user without the proper authorisation.\r\n\r\nYou already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n\r\nSwitch to unix_socket authentication [Y/n] "]
[31.554, "o", "y"]
[1.219, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.101, "o", "Enabled successfully (or at least no errors was emitted)!\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Reloading privilege tables..\r\n"]
[0.086, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n\r\nYou already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n\r\nChange the root password? [Y/n] "]
[5.371, "o", "y"]
[0.587, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.014, "o", "New password: "]
[2.869, "o", "\r\nRe-enter new password: "]
[2.895, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.116, "o", "Password updated successfully!\r\nReloading privilege tables..\r\n"]
[0.083, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n"]
[0.018, "o", "\r\nBy default, a MariaDB installation has an anonymous user, allowing anyone\r\nto log into MariaDB without having to have a user account created for\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "them.  This is intended only for testing, and to make the installation\r\ngo a bit smoother.  You should remove them before moving into a\r\nproduction environment.\r\n\r\nRemove anonymous users? [Y/n] "]
[7.019, "o", "y"]
[0.194, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.100, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "Normally, root should only be allowed to connect from 'localhost'.  This\r\nensures that someone cannot guess at the root password from the network.\r\n\r\nDisallow root login remotely? [Y/n] "]
[0.536, "o", "y"]
[0.520, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.099, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n\r\nBy default, MariaDB comes with a database named 'test' that anyone can\r\naccess.  This is also intended only for testing, and should be removed\r\nbefore moving into a production environment.\r\n\r\nRemove test database and access to it? [Y/n] "]
[0.608, "o", "y"]
[0.297, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", " - Dropping test database...\r\n"]
[0.095, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected, 1 warning\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n - Removing privileges on test database...\r\n"]
[0.100, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Reloading the privilege tables will ensure that all changes made so far\r\nwill take effect immediately.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\nReload privilege tables now? [Y/n] "]
[0.988, "o", "y"]
[0.480, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.086, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Cleaning up...\r\n"]
[0.012, "o", "\r\nAll done!  If you've completed all of the above steps, your MariaDB\r\ninstallation should now be secure.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\nThanks for using MariaDB!\r\n"]
